Articles.Content: One more question I am trying to play with real fuels and Launchers pack (SpaceX). I don't have half the engines from this mod and I can only choose one type of fuel in the tanks. No di configuration for this mod ?

@Briso Mh yeah, RO does not seem to have aupport for this mod. I‘d be grateful if someone took the time and created some proper RO configs for this and integrated it within RO, since it‘s a common request, but you‘ll need to ping the RO dev team there, nothing I can really do about it.

I know that the configs I made up are fairly outdated now... I need to update them, just been busy with IRL stuff and other rockets. I'll attempt to get in contact with one of a RO devs when I get them updated. Not sure what all is required when making configs for them though.

I don't know if it is just meant to be this way, but for some reason my install has fairly low delta v stats for each of the rockets - Falcon Heavy has only about 6000 m/s dV with no payload, and Falcon 9 has only about 5500 m/s with no payload when I would expect them to have probably at least 7000 m/s empty (?). Is there any way I can manually modify the parts to increase the delta-V so that I can lift heavier payloads into orbit?

Thanks a lot.

So when I'm in the part config, I'm just editing the mass = 22 section on the F93_S2FuelTank cfg (for example)? Is this the empty or full mass of the part? What do you recommend I change it to?

Thanks.

17 minutes ago, OswaldiusB said:

So when I'm in the part config, I'm just editing the mass = 22 section on the F93_S2FuelTank cfg (for example)? Is this the empty or full mass of the part? What do you recommend I change it to?

Thanks.

empty the mass number, 22 is the empty mass and the total mass is the empty mass PLUS the LF*0.005 (the density) and the Ox*0.005 and the Monopropellant amount *0.004 for the MP it would be 100*0.004 = 0.4 tonnes (according to this calculator)

according to http://www.spacex.com/falcon9 the second stage burns for 397 seconds (6 minutes, 37 seconds)

another thing is that acctualy the real life F9 can only lift 22t into LEO

How looks your GameData? You need a folder Launchers Pack inside GameData. Inside Launchers Pack there are the folders configs, flags, rockets, sounds. Anything other is wrong. Your link to Firespitter is wrong and is linked to Filter Extensions. Here you can find the newest Firespitter.

You must copy the craftfiles manually to your savegame, not to GameData.

No, you must copy the entire folder "Launchers Pack" to your GameData. It includes all folders and files of this mod. The F9-folder must be from another mod because this mod has no folder calles F9. Only a folder SpaceX, which includes all files of the Falcon 1 and 9.
With F9-Folder I think you mean the F9demo-folder. Yes, this folder must be directly in GameData, But it includes not the real F9 instead of a proposed Demo-version of the F9.
